<subSubSection id="0FC96579FFCC89487D9DA169BFB8FFFC" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="key">
<keyStep id="FC272E57FFCC89487D9DA169BFB8FFFC" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph id="476C36F2FFCC89487D9DA169BFB8FFB2" blockId="26.[151,1436,844,971]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead id="FC2295C7FFCC89487D9DA169BFB8FFB2" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
1a. Ocelli present; posterior margin of crown curving anterad medially; body yellow or green or both in dried specimens, color often arranged in longitudinal stripes on the crown and pronotum (Pl. 4C) 
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFCC89487991A14BBFB8FFB2" box="[1179,1435,878,901]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
..................... 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFCC89487823A14BBFB8FFB2" authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1972" box="[1321,1435,878,901]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Afrorubria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Afrorubria</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="476C36F2FFCC89487D9DA1B4BFB8FFFC" blockId="26.[151,1436,844,971]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead id="FC2295C7FFCC89487D9DA1B4BFB8FFFC" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
1b. Ocelli absent or very reduced and difficult to see; posterior margin of crown subtrapezoidal; body yellowish brown in dried specimens (Pl. 4D) 
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFCC89487CF9A191BFB8FFFC" box="[499,1435,948,971]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
............................................................................................................................... 
